text: Barlyne is a locality in the North Burnett Region, Queensland, Australia. In the , Barlyne had a population of 3 people. == History == In the early 1890s, the Inman family selected land from Gayndah which they called Barlyne. In 1917, the main industry was dairying but there were successful experiments with growing bananas, pawpaws and pineapples. == References == Category:North Burnett Region Category:Localities in Queensland
